CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 6, 1965, p. 24, reads: "Schenley Favored to Win City Cage Crown Friday - City Title Up For Grabs - These players will carry th banners of Schenley and South Hills High Schools, Friday, at Pitt Field House, in the battle for the City League basketball championship.  Members of Schenley's team, left photo are, left to right, front row: Frank Williams, James Prince, Kenny Durrett and Archie McGill.  Back row: Charles Burley, Pete Gibson, Tommy Carroll and Marvin Snowden... - Harris Photos."
TitMainTitle: Members of Schenley High School basketball team, kneeling from left: Frank Williams, James Prince, Kenny Durrett, Archie McGill; standing: Charles Burley, Ed "Pete" Gibson, Tommy Carroll, and Marvin "Marv" Snowden, posed in Gymnasium
